S'  Although greedy layer-wise pre-training has achieved a lot of success in\ntraining deep neural networks, due to the locality of the method higher layer\nof the network may not learn representation that are useful for the original\ninput. In this work, a simple joint method that tries to integrate multiple\nsingle layer training objective into one global objective is proposed. It not\nonly mimics the layer-wise training scheme locally, but also adjust all the\nweights together based on the reconstruction loss from end-to-end. Preliminary\nresults show that it extract more representative features in the unsupervised\nsetting, and also achieved comparable performance in the supervised setting as\ncompared to the greedy layer-wise approach.\n'
