S'  We construct the complete structural phase diagram of polymer adsorption at\nsubstrates with attractive stripe-like patterns in the parameter space spanned\nby the adsorption affinity of the stripes and temperature. Results were\nobtained by extensive generalized-ensemble Monte Carlo simulations of a generic\nmodel for the hybrid organic-inorganic system. By comparing with adhesion\nproperties at homogeneous substrates, we find substantial differences in the\nformation of adsorbed polymer structures if translational invariance at the\nsurface is broken by a regular pattern. Beside a more specific understanding of\npolymer adsorption processes, our results are potentially relevant for the\ndesign of macromolecular pattern recognition devices such as sensors.\n'
